description.narrative: NESDC adopted an official child poverty measure aligned with the SDG requirements to guide policymaking in addressing poverty and inequity for the first time, triggering national interest and discussions at the board of NESDC as well as in top-tier media. Results from the national disability survey inform the situation of children with disabilities for the first time, filling the data gap on the most vulnerable groups of children. Data from MICS 6, which was conducted in 2019 will be available in 2020 allowing for improved monitoring of the SDGs. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
